editorialSummary.text: Casual counter-serve chain serving a variety of chicken wings & sides.

originalText.text: This evening, I arrived at your restaurant to pick up my online order. As I approached the door, I noticed a female cashier at the register, gazing out of the window. As soon as I entered, she quickly left the register area. I walked up to the register, and waited for her to assist me. I noticed she was just playing around  with herself and pretending to be occupied. It took for the other employee who was working in the kitchen area to signal her that I was there. I would describe the cashier's behavior as uncanny and unprofessional while she attended to me. After she handed me my order, she asked me to close the entrance door and I thought that was odd, because shouldn't that be her job? She then went on to explain to me, that the door had mechanical issues. I was not satisfied with her attitude or her basically asking me to do her job for her. It is not the customer's responsibility to close and open doors at the restaurant, that is between management and staff. I can only describe the female employee as a light skinned, Latinx with eyeglasses.

originalText.text: Incredibly disappointing service. I was quoted a 60 min waiting time and I showed up at my designated pickup time and waited for an additional 90 minutes. The employees tried their hardest to make it work, but orders clearly kept coming in and they could not keep up. I left without having received my food, even though i had already paid.

originalText.text: First off, the service that I received was pleasant. Though it seemed like there were only 2 or 3 people working and lots of online orders coming in, I was still attended to in a timely fashion. Now let's get into the food. The wings were alright. Nothing to really write home about but it did its job. The fries, phew. Someone mentioned something about sugar and I don't know why it's done but I definitely tasted some type of sweetness on my fries. Didn't really care for it. I'm sure others like it but it wasn't for me. Anywho, my order didn't take too long but I would suggest ordering for pickup.

originalText.text: Ordered through Frub Hub asked for a brownie and found no brownie in the bag. Called the store and waited 10 minutes for them to pick up the phone. Told the team member what happened and she replied in a very condescending tone we didn’t have anymore brownies so we gave you and extra ranch…..excuse me how is that even a substitute!? We gotta do better.

originalText.text: Worst wing stop ever! I order from this location and they took 2 hours.. two hours for my food. Then they cancelled on me. I called them and no pick up. This is very disappointing & frustrating. I had almost 10 delivery people cancel on me because my food wasn’t ready. I understand it’s busy but 2hours is insane plus no food on top of that.
